Nothing beats a warming bowl of soup on a chilly winter’s day and – with many of us having honed our kitchen skills over the past year – it’s the perfect time to make your own from scratch. Perhaps you’ve got a go-to method for minestrone which always proves a hit during the colder months? Or maybe you’ve mastered the recipe for a moreish chicken noodle soup? Whether you prefer a creamy mushroom concoction or a hearty Cullen skink, we’d love to hear your recommendations and recipes for soups to make at home. You can get in contact with us by filling in the form below. Your responses are secure as the form is encrypted and only the Guardian has access to your contributions. One of our journalists will be in contact with you before we publish any contributions, so please do leave contact details. If you’re having trouble using the form, click here. Read terms of service here.